All these things you have shared is not exclusively a party of wahi culture. This culture is very old predates even before Islam came to these region. Before 70 years it was a part of India and all the food habit and the way of life is similar to the people Living in mountainous region through out the Himalayan belt. 3/4th of Himalaya is still with India. You will find similar features in Jammu & Kashmir, Uttarakhand, Skim Arunchal Pradesh in India. So collectively you can say it is a historical party of South Asia Where India has a deep influence in every thing people do directly or indirectly. In India Each and every village is self dependent and most of the things are locally produce and rest is exported to urban center. Poverty is more in urban center not in villages across India. In our culture we are thought to be satisfied with minimal basic amenities. Excess use and exorbitant way of life is considered to wasteful.

My name is Patrick, I've traveled to some interesting places around the world to find out about things. I dived with dolphins, rays and sea turtles, walked across volcanoes, was traveling in ancient temples, in the hinterland of the Taurus Mountains I encountered rattlesnakes and my personal highlight was the Serra de Tramuntana where I often feel drawn. In doing so, I had to fight my way through impenetrable areas, without which one would have dared to step backwards with the wrong technology. For me, there is nothing more exciting than to spend days wandering around with nature with unknown people and to take successful steps together with simple things and learn new things.
At the campfire you can also look back over the unpleasant moments of life and master together culinary delicacies, which can sometimes taste very strange. Often the people get to know each other anew through this intensive experience with nature and you find yourself again.

My roots are located far back in Catalonia which belongs to Spain, the culture is very much influenced by people who live with nature and not against you. People who make no distinction between rich and poor, attractiveness and unsightliness. Sometimes this Spanish blood comes to light in my temper and a strong sense of justice comes out of me. Are you now scared and you prefer to be attracted to men who want to be men but are not. Or do you also have unbridled temperament in blood and can you engage in a lengthy conversation with me?

Although I do not like English, the pitch is often overbearing, your voice makes me very angry. Your expressions enchant me. I do not know much about you except that I want to feel your breath on my skin, to a very special place.

5:30 This system exist in the Balkans too.. for example as a child me was visiting my grandparents in the village of eastern Macedonia... and me and my gbrandfather use to go with the cows and the sheeps and the goats at different days once every 40 days .. you go as proportionally as the number of heads of animals a household have.. some go more often some less... goats are the hardest !!! Next example ... when you go to water a certain garden crop in certain small valley nearby the village .. in that valley the land is shared by all of the villagers whos side on the village face that valley and when you go there you water everybodys garden vegetables so other do not need to come by.... Next example.. when you lid a fire in a stone owen outside to bake bread... you make and bake the bread for at least 4-5 house-holds nearby the flour is bought and shared together and proportion by familly members is calculated ... THIS IS HOW IT WAS...now it has been 20 years since and now only the old live there... the young moved out for "better life" and they do not realize that they left for worse instead !

Actually Gojal valley is famous for its rich natural wealth, landscape, picturesque locations, lofty mountains, breathtaking scenic beauty, wildlife and nature, glittering glaciers, valleys of lush green foliage and fruits, beautiful meadows, and pastures. The valley is comprised of 25 villages, including Ghawooshben (Ainabad), Shishkat (Nazimabad-1), Gulmit, Ghulkin, Seesoni (Hussani), Passu, Khyber, Ghalapan, Moorkhon, Jamalabad, Gircha, Sarteez, Nazimabad, Sost (Aminabad) Khudabad, Misgar, Qalandarchi, Avgarchi, Raminj, Yarz Rech, Kirmin, Reshit, Sharisafz, Kumpirdior, Zowoodkhon, Oston and Shimshal. Gulmit is Gojalâ€™s largest settlement and Tehsil headquarters.Gojal is geographically the largest Tehsil in Gilgit-Baltistan spreading over an area of about 8,500 sq.km. The valley borders with the Xinjiang-Uighur region of China and Wakhan Corridor or Little Pamir of Afghanistan. Hope in the coming future many tourists will come and explore the beauty of Gojal valley,Gilgit Baltistan , Thank you very much- Mast Ullah Baig Musofer
